This web application is not a "complete" web app, but rather an app built while learning to learn and understand certain functionalities, such as login sessions, user/article models, customizable views, and of course, for fun.
I created this web application using Ruby (3) on Rails (6.1.4) from scratch as part of learning the entire full-stack framework for Ruby on Rails. Sign-Ups work, Logins work. Categories are implemented and uses a many-to-many association. The search algorithm isn't built, not sure it's needed but might do it anyway just to write the functionality once to understand how to build it. The Can't Touch Me link is meant to be disabled, so it won't do anything, hence the name.
